STEP 4 — Controller: emit form_errors as a distinct SSE event
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Just like FORM_WIDGET, the controller intercepts [[FORM_ERRORS:<json>]]
and emits a separate event.

In chat_controller.py, define a second marker + helper:

    FORM_ERRORS_RE = re.compile(r"\[\[FORM_ERRORS:(.*?)\]\]", re.DOTALL)

    def _emit_with_form_errors(full_text: str):
        match = FORM_ERRORS_RE.search(full_text)
        if not match:
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": full_text}
            return
        pre = full_text[:match.start()]
        post = full_text[match.end():]
        raw = match.group(1)
        try:
            payload = json.loads(raw)
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"[FORM-ERRORS] JSON parse error: {e}", flush=True)
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": full_text}
            return
        if pre.strip():
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": pre}
        yield {"type": "form_errors", "form_id": payload.get("form_id"), "errors": payload.get("errors", {})}
        if post.strip():
            yield {"type": "chunk", "text": post}

